##The Yangtze River has been without a rescuer ever since

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu Guanrong

About 3,957 words

Estimated reading time: 10 minutes

By Yin Haiyue, Gong Ayuan

Editor | from Yuhua

Yu guan-rong has spent most of his life saving people.

In 2010, he founded the Wuhan Yangtze Rescue Volunteer Team, which led the team to save more than 700 lives. "I can not see a life disappearing before me, " he said

He knew the Yangtze, where its banks were sloping more than 30 degrees, where the moss was thickest and slippiest, and where the underside of the steps was hollowed out by the water. He calls the "triangle" , a 50-metre backwash of the Yellow Crane Tower Wharf, the most dangerous part of Wuhan's waters, where he and his companions saved 24 lives in 2014.

He once described how, when he first saved someone as a young man, "that man pressed your shoulder into the water, " and how he could not forget the horrible look in his eyes, which was a "survival instinct. ".

He can hold it underwater for 3 minutes and 20 seconds. But at 9:30 a.m. on February 6th, he didn't hold his breath. Yu Guanrong, 71, died of pneumonia, which had not been diagnosed before his death.

In the last days of his life, he left a message to his friend: "A superfluous word, a superfluous action can make people gasp for breath. ".

His wife, Wang Tianrong, said: "He saved his whole life, and when he finally needed saving, even his relatives had no way. "

1

A few days before his illness, Yu Guanrong went to Chengdu to attend rescue training. Before he left, he told Hao Zhenhai, the rescue team on the follow-up development, oneself have a lot of ideas, come back and communicate with everyone. Unexpectedly, this was the last time the two met.

In the circle, the big man Yu Guanrong is a well-known bodybuilder. He runs marathons and crosses the Yangtze River. His wife can not lift a Dumbbell at home. He does not play Mahjong or drink alcohol. He does not have a single white hair. People say he "must live to be at least 90 years old. ".

At first, no one associated him with new coronary pneumonia.

Wife Wang Tianrong remember January 11 that day, Yu Guanrong went out with old classmates party, play all day, after going home in the evening said a little cold, "soon began to runny nose. ". She gave her husband, who rarely took medication, cold medicine for two days and "drank lots of boiling water. ".

He went to work on Monday, January 13th.

On January 16, Wang Tianrong found that Yu Guanrong not only did not get better with a cold, cough, but also a little wheezing, body joints also a little pain, "like listlessness. ". Take his temperature. He's got a fever of 102.

On the morning of January 17, they went to the Concord Hospital, hung up the general outpatient clinic, but also took a film, the doctor told them, Yu Guanrong lung infection, to injection, "three days in a row, hit three CEPHALOSPORINS. ".

However, after the injection, Yu Guanrong's body showed no signs of improvement. Wang Tianrong later regretted, at that time, she let her husband to find a doctor for imported medicine, but Yu Guanrong refused, said, "buy some vitamin C Yinqiao tablets, boil some brown sugar water at home to drink. ".

"At that time, we saw a doctor in Concord. We didn't even mention the fever clinic or the new coronary pneumonia. We didn't even think about it, " Wang said.

Yu Guanrong sick these days, but also the Wuhan epidemic notification of the blank period. From January 12 to January 17, the Wuhan Health Commission said there were no new cases. On January 19, Wuhan reported 136 new cases overnight, but the news said: the infection is not strong, the epidemic can be prevented and controlled.

Until January 22, Wang Tianrong found that her husband's condition began to worsen, high fever to 39 degrees Celsius, to the Concord Hospital to see a doctor again, her husband sitting on the bench, head against the wall, "smacked his mouth panting. ". But this time, the doctor told her to go to the fever clinic immediately.

The doctor told Yu Guanrong to have an injection for two days. On the 23rd, when Wuhan was closed to the public, there were no subways or buses in the city, so she and Yu Guanrong shared a bicycle to see a doctor. Wang Tianrong saw his wife, who was out of breath, riding her bicycle to the left and right, like twisting twist twist twist twist.

The next day was New Year's Eve, and her daughter took them to the Red Cross Hospital. Wang Tianrong said, the hospital people next to each other, even the seat is very difficult to find. He had a fever of 103, didn't want to talk, sat in a place where the wind wouldn't blow, and put his head against the wall. That day in the rain, Wang Tianrong with an umbrella to stand outside, the line is very long, half a day move a, with the front people stick, people are anxious to die. 10:00 in the morning, shot up to 4:00 in the morning to go home.

Wang Tianrong said that he suspected that his wife may be infected at that time. On January 26, she accompanied Yu to Wuhan Red Cross hospital for a CT scan. Doctors told them that Yu had "severe lung infections" and that he had lost the strength to climb the stairs. Hao Zhenhai to call him, Yu Guanrong bluntly "too uncomfortable" , every two minutes to drink water, the mouth of the phlegm pressure down, "or not smooth suction.

On the 27th, he couldn't put on his socks and pants by himself, and he was so out of breath that he couldn't lift his feet after walking for half an hour for 5 minutes.

Wang Tianrong has repeatedly to the hospital, the community for help, hoping to be Yu Guanrong arrangements in hospital, have no results. On January 29, with the help of a friend, Yu Guanrong was finally admitted to the Sixth Hospital in Wuhan. Wang Tianrong breathed a sigh of relief and said, "the Iron Tuo in my heart fell to the ground. " She ran three blocks to buy noodles for her husband, but did not expect it, that was the last time I saw him.

2

News of Yu's death spread quickly through the rescue circle on Feb. 6. Zhang Jianmin, 64, cried all morning.

Zhang Jianmin was the second leader of the Yangtze Rescue Team. He said, old Yu never lost his temper, loyalty, always smiling, "we all like him. ".

In 2010, Yu gathered people online to form a rescue team and "passed on some rescue experience to each other. " More than 100 people joined the team, and Yu was elected team leader with a unanimous vote, Zhang recalled.

By 2010, Wuhan was suffering more than 100 drowning deaths a year on average, according to Wuhan's Water Public Security Bureau. Between 2010 and 2013, the number dropped to about 60 a year, and in 2014, the number of drowning accidents dropped to more than 20.

Zhang Jianmin said that before everybody is relies on one cavity enthusiasm to save a person, "has not grasped the science rescue method" .

Yu guan-rong wants to find a rescue system. Hao Zhenhai, 54, is the head of the Yangtze Rescue Team's training department. Yu Guanrong took him to Beijing to participate in emergency rescue courses, to the Red Cross to do volunteers, to learn first aid knowledge, "we learn, then to teach others. ".

Yu Guanrong said: "A rescue team alone in the Yangtze River rescue or not comprehensive, should be trained up, two legs walk together. " The first lesson of training is cardiopulmonary resuscitation.

3

CPR has always been his deepest "pimple. ".

In 2005, Yu's 23-year-old son was accidentally electrocuted while carrying an electric fan to work. "This thing hit him very hard. " Wang Tianrong remembers, Yu Guanrong sitting on the SOFA, 3 days do not eat, do not drink, let tears and runny nose.

For a long time, he cried on the bus, in the rain, in the middle of the night, thinking that if someone had given CPR to his son who had gone into cardiac arrest, he might not have died.

He went alone to Everest, he said, where the mountains are closest to the sky, climb to the top of the mountain, can be closer to his son.

At Everest Base Camp, Yu Guanrong found that good climbers have made a variety of contingency plans in advance, they look the most not afraid of death, in fact, they respect life most, they will use all means to "live. ".

"Mountain climbing changed him, " Wang said. "There's still a lot to do, " he felt

Teammates of the Yangtze Rescue Team became Yu Guanrong's first students.

Team members have saved lives, and watched them die in their own hands. In 2002, they rescued a drowning college student, rescued after the shore, Hao Zhenhai Eyes looked at the student's face from blue to black, more than 10 minutes later, his nose, mouth began to bleed, and so on emergency doctors arrived, a touch of carotid artery, there is no sign of life. The doctor asked him, did you give him CPR?

"Won't do, DARE NOT DO! " Hao Zhenhai says, at that time he can dial 120 only.

Then people started training in first aid. Hao Zhenhai training is very nervous, afraid of speaking wrong, Yu Guanrong encouraged him, you just speak, speak wrong I give you correct, if you do not speak, never on the stage. Later, Hao Zhenhai every year to speak a few hundred, "disciples teach disciples. "

Instead of just standing on the riverbank with their feet wet, they go to schools and communities, teach residents how to prevent fires and electric shocks, teach seniors how to prevent cardiovascular disease, and deal with bleeding and burns.

In Yu Guanrong's view, every life saved, is to save a family. His goal is "to minimize the number of family tragedies in cities that result from drowning. ".

Yu Guanrong also advocated the concept of first aid equipment. He said that it is very easy to meet danger when jumping into water to save people. He advocated that people should learn to use bamboo poles, life preservers, throwing rope bags and other equipment when saving people. In an emergency, a plastic water bottle, a piece of foam, and a volleyball, even a finger-sized branch can do the trick.

In his mind, the only way to save someone is to protect your own life. In 2014 alone, he saved 52 people from drowning.

Since May 2014, the Yangtze River Rescue Team has introduced a duty-on-duty system, which operates at eight duty stations with fixed time and fixed points. Today, there are 20 regular guard points along the banks of the two rivers.

Ren Jiantao, a professor at Renmin University of China, once described the Yangtze rescue team as a modern organizational behavior that transcended individual heroism.

Yu Guanrong also cast his eyes abroad. In 2012, Zhou Hanming was invited by the World Ice Swimming Association to compete in a relay race in the Bering Strait. Zhou Hanming did not want to go at first, Yu advised him, during the race, foreign swimmers will take some emergency rescue measures, "you contact them, you can see, learn. "

"He left early. If he had 10 years... " Zhou Hanming said.

4

After Yu was hospitalized, both men spent the longest nine days of their lives. Until Yu Guanrong died, Wang Tianrong also could not see him one eye. She could only listen to her husband's voice growing fainter and fainter over the phone.

On the 3rd day of Hospitalization, Yu Guanrong called his wife, his tone was very difficult, he said, I can not leave the suction machine, and can not stand up, the hand is also boring, because the medical care is too busy, my urinal and Bedpan they are too late to pour, can you come in and help me?

"When I heard his voice, I was so worried. I rode my bike to the hospital. " But the nurse wouldn't let the family into the ward, so she had to buy two washbasins and pass them in to her wife instead of the BEDPAN.

Yu Guanrong died, Wang Tianrong found, pass in the wash basin and towel are clean as new, even did not move paper towels.

This lets Wang Tianrong feel painful, he so loves a clean person. Every day to wash hair, bath, before going to work, but also with water to hair shun walk again. Eat Fruit, wash it and soak it in salt water.

Two days before he left, he telephoned to say, go and buy him a Adult diaper. Wang Tianrong, 70, cries as she searches for diapers at a supermarket. She said she had never used it and didn't know what it looked like. Holding a diaper, she begged the nurse to let her into the ward, but was rebuffed.

Speaking of which, she broke down in tears and told reporters on the phone: "I think he suffered more psychologically than he might have suffered from the disease. "

Until the last moment of life, Wang Tianrong also do not know, whether the husband really died of new crown pneumonia. She once told Yu Guanrong telephone, let him ask the hospital to do nucleic acid testing, Yu Guanrong said, the doctor told him not to do, certainly.

February 4, Yu Guanrong telephone instructions will, the voice is very slow very weak, the wife is not very clear. He told Wang Tianrong, to take good care of themselves, his last go also do not rescue, do not cut the throat cut trachea, the ashes sprinkled in the Dragon King Temple outside the river.

It was at the confluence of the Han River and Yangtze rivers, where he used to swim and where he saved many lives.

Wang Tianrong said, Yu Guanrong like singing, singing opera, Peking Opera, Yue Opera, huangmei opera, he can sing. He can also dance, play the accordion, Erhu.

Hao Zhenhai said, "as long as there is a disaster, he shouldered the bag to go. " In 2015, "star of the East" sank, Yu Guanrong early morning contact team members, rushed to save people. In 2016, a flood broke out in many places in Hubei Province. Yu Guanrong drove a private car and took a storm boat to help move the victims. Hao Zhenhai still remember, he stood on two feet in the water, carrying the scene of the victims ashore.

"He saved a lot of lives in his life, " Zhou Hanming said, but he said it was "normal" to save people.

Yu Guanrong's micro blog is called "big something" . A friend once asked him the origin of his screen name. He explained that "something" was a stone block and a stepping stone under a pillar, meaning a pillar of stability.
